    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_1A6D3E30-2212-0135-1DC4-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>If you want to add a page to a Mastery Path in a module, you must first allow the page in Mastery Paths. Otherwise, the page will not appear as a conditional item when you <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-add-conditional-content-to-a-Mastery-Path-source-item/ta-p/854" target="_blank">add an item to a </a>Mastery Path.</p>
<p><strong>Notes:</strong> </p>
<ul>
<li>The Mastery Paths setting can be <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-set-details-for-a-course/ta-p/1037" target="_blank">managed in your course</a> if the setting has been <a href="/t5/Admin-Guide/How-do-I-set-details-for-an-account/ta-p/194" target="_blank">enabled by your institution</a>.</li>
<li>If you allow a page in Mastery Paths, the page will not be visible to students until it is added to a Mastery Path.</li>
<li>Course items such as links, files, and media content must be embedded in a page or assignment to be used as conditional content in Mastery Paths.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_modules" data-step-uuid="3aeb5f72-6633-4cc4-be46-be03510eb028">
